{"name":"Mathlib.Combinatorics.Hall.Basic","instances":[{"typeNames":["Set.Elem","Subtype","Membership.mem","Finset","Finset.instMembershipFinset","hallMatchingsOn"],"name":"hallMatchingsOn.finite","className":"Finite"},{"typeNames":["Set.Elem","Rel.image","Finset.toSet"],"name":"instFintypeElemImageToSet","className":"Fintype"}],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Combinatorics.Hall.Finite","Mathlib.CategoryTheory.CofilteredSystem","Mathlib.Data.Rel"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L216-L228","name":"Fintype.all_card_le_filter_rel_iff_exists_injective","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#Fintype.all_card_le_filter_rel_iff_exists_injective","doc":"This is a version of **Hall's Marriage Theorem** in terms of a relation to a finite type.\nThere is a transversal of the relation (an injective function `α → β` whose graph is a subrelation\nof the relation) iff every subset of `k` terms of `α` is related to at least `k` terms of `β`.\n\nIt is like `Fintype.all_card_le_rel_image_card_iff_exists_injective` but uses `Finset.filter`\nrather than `Rel.image`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L190-L205","name":"Fintype.all_card_le_rel_image_card_iff_exists_injective","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#Fintype.all_card_le_rel_image_card_iff_exists_injective","doc":"This is a version of **Hall's Marriage Theorem** in terms of a relation\nbetween types `α` and `β` such that `α` is finite and the image of\neach `x : α` is finite (it suffices for `β` to be finite; see\n`Fintype.all_card_le_filter_rel_iff_exists_injective`).  There is\na transversal of the relation (an injective function `α → β` whose graph is\na subrelation of the relation) iff every subset of\n`k` terms of `α` is related to at least `k` terms of `β`.\n\nNote: if `[Fintype β]`, then there exist instances for `[∀ (a : α), Fintype (Rel.image r {a})]`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L171-L178","name":"instFintypeElemImageToSet","kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#instFintypeElemImageToSet","doc":"Given a relation such that the image of every singleton set is finite, then the image of every\nfinite set is finite. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L126-L166","name":"Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_exists_injective","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_exists_injective","doc":"This is the version of **Hall's Marriage Theorem** in terms of indexed\nfamilies of finite sets `t : ι → Finset α`.  It states that there is a\nset of distinct representatives if and only if every union of `k` of the\nsets has at least `k` elements.\n\nRecall that `s.biUnion t` is the union of all the sets `t i` for `i ∈ s`.\n\nThis theorem is bootstrapped from `Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_exists_injective'`,\nwhich has the additional constraint that `ι` is a `Fintype`.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L100-L113","name":"hallMatchingsOn.finite","kind":"instance","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#hallMatchingsOn.finite","doc":""},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L94-L97","name":"hallMatchingsFunctor","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#hallMatchingsFunctor","doc":"This is the `hallMatchingsOn` sets assembled into a directed system.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L80-L89","name":"hallMatchingsOn.nonempty","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#hallMatchingsOn.nonempty","doc":"When the Hall condition is satisfied, the set of matchings on a finite set is nonempty.\nThis is where `Finset.all_card_le_biUnion_card_iff_existsInjective'` comes into the argument. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L69-L75","name":"hallMatchingsOn.restrict","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#hallMatchingsOn.restrict","doc":"Given a matching on a finset, construct the restriction of that matching to a subset. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.lean#L64-L65","name":"hallMatchingsOn","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Combinatorics/Hall/Basic.html#hallMatchingsOn","doc":"The set of matchings for `t` when restricted to a `Finset` of `ι`. "}]}